{
  "id": "phekb-venous-thromboembolism-anticoag-without-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "venous-thromboembolism",
  "name": "VTE - Anticoagulant WITHOUT Diagnosis (Negation / AFib Cohort)",
  "description": "**Negation test.** Find patients on therapeutic anticoagulants who do NOT have a venous thromboembolism diagnosis. These are typically patients on long-term anticoagulation for atrial fibrillation, mechanical valves, or post-op DVT prophylaxis \u2014 clinically distinct from VTE patients but carrying the same bleeding risk. FHIR R4 doesn't natively support `NOT EXISTS` in queries, so the canonical solution is a two-query subtraction: anticoag patients minus VTE-diagnosed patients. Tests whether LLM understands the FHIR negation idiom.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed anticoagulant medications (warfarin, apixaban, rivaroxaban, dabigatran, or enoxaparin) who do NOT have a formal venous thromboembolism diagnosis. The intent is to identify patients on long-term anticoagulation for non-VTE indications such as atrial fibrillation stroke prevention or mechanical heart valve prophylaxis.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on blood thinners without a clot diagnosis.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed therapeutic anticoagulants (warfarin, DOACs, LMWH) who do NOT have a venous thromboembolism diagnosis. FHIR R4 does not natively support negative chains, so this requires a two-query subtraction approach: patients on anticoagulants MINUS patients with VTE diagnoses.",
    "expert": "I need set difference: MedicationRequest?code=anticoags MINUS Condition?code=VTE-codes (at the patient level). FHIR doesn't support `NOT EXISTS` natively, so two queries are required: (1) `MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|11289,1364430,1114195,1037042,67108` to get anticoag patients, (2) `Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|128053003,234044007,281595001,59282003,234049002` to get VTE-diagnosed patients, then return query 1 patient set MINUS query 2 patient set."
  },
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "negation": true,
    "algorithm_path": "negation-via-subtraction",
